<subSubSection pageId="411" pageNumber="412" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="411" pageNumber="412">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName LSID="F312B443-D51B-55C2-9E26-F25415C35E63" authority="Casey, 1918" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Peryphodes)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Peryphodes">Peryphodes Casey, 1918</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="411" pageNumber="412" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="411" pageNumber="412">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Peryphodes</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 85. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ochthedromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippiger">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Ochthedromus ephippiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1852 by original designation (see Casey 1918: 89). Etymology. From the generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Peryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the Greek suffix - 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">odes</emphasis>
(likeness), alluding to the resemblance of the adults to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="411" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Peryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="411" pageNumber="412" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Two North American species in the temperate regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="411" pageNumber="412" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="411" pageNumber="412">Lindroth (1963b: 345-346) treated both species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
